<recipe>
    <name>Chicken Cafreal</name>
    <indexCharacter>c</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>0</servings>
    <instructions>1. Wash, remove skin, trim and cut the chicken into eight medium sized pieces. Make deep incisions on the chicken using a sharp knife.

2. Peel, wash and finely slice onions. Heat sufficient oil in a pan and deep fry onions until they are crisp and golden brown. Drain on a paper towel and reserve for garnish.

3. Remove stems and wash green chillies. Peel and wash ginger and garlic.

4. Dry roast coriander seeds, cumin seeds, cloves, green cardamoms, peppercorns and cinnamon. Grind ginger, garlic, green chillies and roasted masala to a paste using a little water.

5. Add salt to the paste and apply this paste to the chicken and refrigerate for two to three hours.

6. Heat three tablespoons of oil in a pan, add the marinated chicken and cooik, covered on medium heat, stirring occasionally. Add a little water if required to avoid scorching. Cook for eight to ten minutes.
7. When almost done add vinegar and simmer for two to three minutes.
8. Serve hot garnished with fried onions.

Chef's tip: If you like you can add a little fresh coriander to the paste. I know of a Goan restaurant which does it and it tastes delicious.</instructions>
